91 // Detect support for r-value references (move semantic).
92 // Move semantic should be enabled with great care in multi-threading environments,
93 // especially if MPFR uses custom memory allocators.
94 // Everything should be thread-safe and support passing ownership over thread boundary.
95 #if (__has_feature(cxx_rvalue_references) || \
96  defined(__GXX_EXPERIMENTAL_CXX0X__) || __cplusplus >= 201103L || \
97  (defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER >= 1600) && !defined(MPREAL_DISABLE_MOVE_SEMANTIC))
98 
99  #define MPREAL_HAVE_MOVE_SUPPORT
100 
101  // Use fields in mpfr_t structure to check if it was initialized / set dummy initialization
102  #define mpfr_is_initialized(x) (0 != (x)->_mpfr_d)
103  #define mpfr_set_uninitialized(x) ((x)->_mpfr_d = 0 )
104 #endif
105 
106 // Detect support for explicit converters.
107 #if (__has_feature(cxx_explicit_conversions) || \
108  (defined(__GXX_EXPERIMENTAL_CXX0X__) && __GNUC_MINOR >= 5) || __cplusplus >= 201103L || \
109  (defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER >= 1800) || \
110  (defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) && __INTEL_COMPILER >= 1300))
111 
112  #define MPREAL_HAVE_EXPLICIT_CONVERTERS

587 }

590 {
591  mpfr_init2(mpfr_ptr(),mpfr_get_prec(u.mpfr_srcptr()));
592  mpfr_set (mpfr_ptr(),u.mpfr_srcptr(),mpreal::get_default_rnd());
593 
594  MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
595 }

597 #ifdef MPREAL_HAVE_MOVE_SUPPORT
598 inline mpreal::mpreal(mpreal&& other)
599 {
600  mpfr_set_uninitialized(mpfr_ptr()); // make sure "other" holds null-pointer (in uninitialized state)
601  mpfr_swap(mpfr_ptr(), other.mpfr_ptr());
602 
603  MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
604 }
605 
606 inline mpreal& mpreal::operator=(mpreal&& other)
607 {
608  if (this != &other)
609  {
610  mpfr_swap(mpfr_ptr(), other.mpfr_ptr()); // destructor for "other" will be called just afterwards
611  MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
612  }
613  return *this;
614 }
615 #endif

623  else

761  // Use SFINAE to restrict arithmetic operations instantiation only for numeric types
762  // This is needed for smooth integration with libraries based on expression templates, like Eigen.
763  // TODO: Do the same for boolean operators.
764  template <typename ArgumentType> struct result_type {};
765 
766  template <> struct result_type<mpreal> {typedef mpreal type;};
767  template <> struct result_type<mpz_t> {typedef mpreal type;};
768  template <> struct result_type<mpq_t> {typedef mpreal type;};
769  template <> struct result_type<long double> {typedef mpreal type;};
770  template <> struct result_type<double> {typedef mpreal type;};
771  template <> struct result_type<unsigned long int> {typedef mpreal type;};
772  template <> struct result_type<unsigned int> {typedef mpreal type;};
773  template <> struct result_type<long int> {typedef mpreal type;};
774  template <> struct result_type<int> {typedef mpreal type;};
775  template <> struct result_type<long long> {typedef mpreal type;};
776  template <> struct result_type<unsigned long long> {typedef mpreal type;};
777 }

926 inline mpreal& mpreal::operator=(const mpreal& v)
927 {
928  if (this != &v)
929  {
930  mp_prec_t tp = mpfr_get_prec( mpfr_srcptr());
931  mp_prec_t vp = mpfr_get_prec(v.mpfr_srcptr());
932 
933  if(tp != vp){
934  clear(mpfr_ptr());
935  mpfr_init2(mpfr_ptr(), vp);
936  }
937 
938  mpfr_set(mpfr_ptr(), v.mpfr_srcptr(), mpreal::get_default_rnd());
939 
940  MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
941  }
942  return *this;
943 }

1043  // Use other converters for more precise control on base & precision & rounding:
1044  //
1045  // mpreal(const char* s, mp_prec_t prec, int base, mp_rnd_t mode)
1046  // mpreal(const std::string& s,mp_prec_t prec, int base, mp_rnd_t mode)
1047  //
1048  // Here we assume base = 10 and we use precision of target variable.
1049 
1050  mpfr_t t;
1051 
1052  mpfr_init2(t, mpfr_get_prec(mpfr_srcptr()));
1053 
1054  if(0 == mpfr_set_str(t, s, 10, mpreal::get_default_rnd()))
1055  {
1056  mpfr_set(mpfr_ptr(), t, mpreal::get_default_rnd());
1057  MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
1058  }
1059 
1060  clear(t);
1061  return *this;
1062 }

1774 inline std::string mpreal::toString(int n, int b, mp_rnd_t mode) const
1775 {
1776  // TODO: Add extended format specification (f, e, rounding mode) as it done in output operator
1777  (void)b;
1778  (void)mode;
1779 
1780 #if (MPFR_VERSION >= MPFR_VERSION_NUM(2,4,0))
1781 
1782  std::ostringstream format;
1783 
1784  int digits = (n >= 0) ? n : 2 + bits2digits(mpfr_get_prec(mpfr_srcptr()));
1785 
1786  format << "%." << digits << "RNg";
1787 
1788  return toString(format.str());
1789 
1790 #else
1791 
1792  char *s, *ns = NULL;
1793  size_t slen, nslen;
1794  mp_exp_t exp;
1795  std::string out;
1796 
1797  if(mpfr_inf_p(mp))
1798  {
1799  if(mpfr_sgn(mp)>0) return "+Inf";
1800  else return "-Inf";
1801  }
1802 
1803  if(mpfr_zero_p(mp)) return "0";
1804  if(mpfr_nan_p(mp)) return "NaN";
1805 
1806  s = mpfr_get_str(NULL, &exp, b, 0, mp, mode);
1807  ns = mpfr_get_str(NULL, &exp, b, (std::max)(0,n), mp, mode);
1808 
1809  if(s!=NULL && ns!=NULL)
1810  {
1811  slen = strlen(s);
1812  nslen = strlen(ns);
1813  if(nslen<=slen)
1814  {
1815  mpfr_free_str(s);
1816  s = ns;
1817  slen = nslen;
1818  }
1819  else {
1820  mpfr_free_str(ns);
1821  }
1822 
1823  // Make human eye-friendly formatting if possible
1824  if (exp>0 && static_cast<size_t>(exp)<slen)
1825  {
1826  if(s[0]=='-')
1827  {
1828  // Remove zeros starting from right end
1829  char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1830  while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s+exp) ptr--;
1831 
1832  if(ptr==s+exp) out = std::string(s,exp+1);
1833  else out = std::string(s,exp+1)+'.'+std::string(s+exp+1,ptr-(s+exp+1)+1);
1834 
1835  //out = string(s,exp+1)+'.'+string(s+exp+1);
1836  }
1837  else
1838  {
1839  // Remove zeros starting from right end
1840  char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1841  while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s+exp-1) ptr--;
1842 
1843  if(ptr==s+exp-1) out = std::string(s,exp);
1844  else out = std::string(s,exp)+'.'+std::string(s+exp,ptr-(s+exp)+1);
1845 
1846  //out = string(s,exp)+'.'+string(s+exp);
1847  }
1848 
1849  }else{ // exp<0 || exp>slen
1850  if(s[0]=='-')
1851  {
1852  // Remove zeros starting from right end
1853  char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1854  while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s+1) ptr--;
1855 
1856  if(ptr==s+1) out = std::string(s,2);
1857  else out = std::string(s,2)+'.'+std::string(s+2,ptr-(s+2)+1);
1858 
1859  //out = string(s,2)+'.'+string(s+2);
1860  }
1861  else
1862  {
1863  // Remove zeros starting from right end
1864  char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1865  while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s) ptr--;
1866 
1867  if(ptr==s) out = std::string(s,1);
1868  else out = std::string(s,1)+'.'+std::string(s+1,ptr-(s+1)+1);
1869 
1870  //out = string(s,1)+'.'+string(s+1);
1871  }
1872 
1873  // Make final string
1874  if(--exp)
1875  {
1876  if(exp>0) out += "e+"+mpfr::toString<mp_exp_t>(exp,std::dec);
1877  else out += "e"+mpfr::toString<mp_exp_t>(exp,std::dec);
1878  }
1879  }
1880 
1881  mpfr_free_str(s);
1882  return out;
1883  }else{
1884  return "conversion error!";
1885  }
1886 #endif
1887 }

1902  'g');

1908  mpfr::mpreal::get_default_rnd(),
1909  mpfr_srcptr())
1910  < 0))
1911  {
1912  os << std::string(s);
1913  mpfr_free_str(s);

1933 // Bits - decimal digits relation
1934 // bits = ceil(digits*log[2](10))
1935 // digits = floor(bits*log[10](2))
1936 
1937 inline mp_prec_t digits2bits(int d)
1938 {
1939  const double LOG2_10 = 3.3219280948873624;
1940 
1941  return mp_prec_t(std::ceil( d * LOG2_10 ));
1942 }
1943 
1944 inline int bits2digits(mp_prec_t b)
1945 {
1946  const double LOG10_2 = 0.30102999566398119;
1947 
1948  return int(std::floor( b * LOG10_2 ));
1949 }

2062 inline mpreal machine_epsilon(mp_prec_t prec)
2063 {
2064  /* the smallest eps such that 1 + eps != 1 */
2065  return machine_epsilon(mpreal(1, prec));
2066 }
2067 
2068 inline mpreal machine_epsilon(const mpreal& x)
2069 {
2070  /* the smallest eps such that x + eps != x */
2071  if( x < 0)
2072  {
2073  return nextabove(-x) + x;
2074  }else{
2075  return nextabove( x) - x;
2076  }
2077 }

2079 // minval is 'safe' meaning 1 / minval does not overflow
2080 inline mpreal minval(mp_prec_t prec)
2081 {
2082  /* min = 1/2 * 2^emin = 2^(emin - 1) */
2083  return mpreal(1, prec) << mpreal::get_emin()-1;
2084 }
2085 
2086 // maxval is 'safe' meaning 1 / maxval does not underflow
2087 inline mpreal maxval(mp_prec_t prec)
2088 {
2089  /* max = (1 - eps) * 2^emax, eps is machine epsilon */
2090  return (mpreal(1, prec) - machine_epsilon(prec)) << mpreal::get_emax();
2091 }

2441 inline const mpreal hypot(const mpreal& a, const mpreal& b, const mpreal& c)
2442 {
2443  if(isnan(a) || isnan(b) || isnan(c)) return mpreal().setNan();
2444  else
2445  {
2446  mpreal absa = abs(a), absb = abs(b), absc = abs(c);
2447  mpreal w = (std::max)(absa, (std::max)(absb, absc));
2448  mpreal r;
2449 
2450  if (!iszero(w))
2451  {
2452  mpreal iw = 1/w;
2453  r = w * sqrt(sqr(absa*iw) + sqr(absb*iw) + sqr(absc*iw));
2454  }
2455 
2456  return r;
2457  }
2458 }

2609 inline const mpreal mod (const mpreal& x, const mpreal& y, mp_rnd_t rnd_mode = mpreal::get_default_rnd())
2610 {
2611  (void)rnd_mode;
2612 
2613  /*
2614 
2615  m = mod(x,y) if y != 0, returns x - n*y where n = floor(x/y)
2616 
2617  The following are true by convention:
2618  - mod(x,0) is x
2619  - mod(x,x) is 0
2620  - mod(x,y) for x != y and y != 0 has the same sign as y.
2621 
2622  */
2623 
2624  if(iszero(y)) return x;
2625  if(x == y) return 0;
2626 
2627  mpreal m = x - floor(x / y) * y;
2628 
2629  return copysign(abs(m),y); // make sure result has the same sign as Y
2630 }

2829 // Uniformly distributed random number generation
2830 // a = random(seed); <- initialization & first random number generation
2831 // a = random(); <- next random numbers generation
2832 // seed != 0
2833 inline const mpreal random(unsigned int seed = 0)
2834 {
2835 #if (MPFR_VERSION >= MPFR_VERSION_NUM(3,0,0))
2836  static gmp_randstate_t state;
2837  static bool initialize = true;
2838 
2839  if(initialize)
2840  {
2841  gmp_randinit_default(state);
2842  gmp_randseed_ui(state,0);
2843  initialize = false;
2844  }
2845 
2846  if(seed != 0) gmp_randseed_ui(state,seed);
2847 
2848  return mpfr::urandom(state);
2849 #else
2850  if(seed != 0) std::srand(seed);
2851  return mpfr::mpreal(std::rand()/(double)RAND_MAX);
2852 #endif
2853 }
